{"title": "Leakage of sensitive information in logger message", "summary": "  Leaking sensitive data to loggers is a common cause of data leaks and can lead to data breaches. This rule looks for instances of sensitive data sent to loggers. ", "description": "\n\nLeaking sensitive data to loggers is a common cause of data leaks and can lead to data breaches. This rule looks for instances of sensitive data sent to loggers.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid using sensitive data in logger messages:\n\n```javascript\nlogger.info(`User is: ${user.email}`)\n```\n\n\u2705 If you need to identify a user, use their unique identifier instead of their personal identifiable information:\n\n```javascript\nlogger.info(`User is: ${user.uuid}`)\n```", "taxonomy": ["CWE-532"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_lang_logger", "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Logging_Cheat_Sheet.html"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}